Hello, how am I, I am OK, thanks. How old am I, I am in my mid 20s. My name is Sarah Williams.

 I have come in today because I am having some problems. I have come for an eye test today because I am getting double vision again.

I have come in today because I am having some problems. I have come for an eye test today because I am getting double vision again. The double vision is really bothering me and I can't make it back into one image whereas before I could. I only get the double vision when I am reading in the evenings. I love reading and do it most nights, but this is when I notice the double vision.

I get the double vision when reading at night quite frequently, particularly if I am tired. This time, I first noticed it about one month ago. The double vision is not getting worse, the only think that makes it go away is if I look into the distance.

When I get the double vision I often get headaches too, quite bad ones and I often have to take paracetamol. The headaches are at the top front middle of my head to start with and then they move down to the back of my head, like a mohawk I would describe it as. The headaches started around the same time as the double vision, about one month ago, although I used to get some headaches before that.

 I don't get any flashing lights or floaters in my vision. I wear my glasses all the time.

 I do have quite a complicated history with my eyes, it all started when I was very young, and I had two surgeries on my eyes. I think they put Botox in before too, I found that really funny like what they use for face lifts in my eyes! Who would have thought!

I have my notes from the surgery here, sorry I can't remember what I had done without this, but it is 6mm off the Left Medial rectus and they moved the position of the Lateral rectus. I also had to wear a cover or patch over my eyes for a couple of years when I was a child. I also had some triangle prism things put into my glasses too.

I haven't had any other eye problems, just the turn in my eye and surgery when I was a kid.

 My family also have health conditions, my grandparents have heart disease and high blood pressure, no one has arthritis or diabetes.

It helps I can drive myself to practice netball now I've passed my test too, so I can go to as many netball training sessions as I want without relying on lifts from other people.
